		<div id="post_message_1228620">
                  
                  I agree that focus swapping and constantly switching stances is highly irrating and sub-optimal.  It is difficult to enjoy the game if you must incessantly switch out equipment.  The main reason I made the thread is that the idea of placing the barriers in such a place while trying to setup a particular types of icons could act as sort of a type of aesthetic experiment.  This probably seems eccentric to many who read this thread.  I have been checking out various UIs and other customization options.     <br />
<br />
As a side note Force Barrier and Chromatic Barrier don't see quite enough use since Fire Barrier's energy regen is so vital when soloing and the haste is often preferable to the defensive advantages of the other two.  Force Barrier is decent compared to the first Fire Barrier and from the second Fire Barrier on it sees less and less use.  It does have situations in which it is useful however these aren't very frequent.  Chromatic Barrier is very nice against caster npcs which should be more prevalant then they currently are.  When energy regened buff Force B and CB become more viable choices though in most cases Fire Barrier has greater efficiency.  In a group the sorcerer usually isn't getting hit so even use of CB can be difficult to justify.     <br />
<br />
I do not want to see switching out these barriers in combat or even after every fight though it would be interesting to create more situations in which, when walking in a specific zone, the other two might be superior for extended use.
                  
		</div>
