		<div id="post_message_1228802">
                  
                  I agree with Emilia; sorcerers shouldn't have stances, period. The barriers are situational buffs, nothing more, nothing less, and should have no other restrictions on them. I am decidedly <i>not</i> in favor of limiting them or restricting them in any other way.<br />
<br />
By all rights, a true stance should not be something you can dance from one to another with in battle. There should be a cool down at least, and a not-in-combat restriction; choose your stance before you engage. This makes sense for melee fighters, or dual-purpose casters like BM's, but not for sorcerers. We are talking about a secondary ability here, not our prime role, which is to blow stuff up.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
