</div>
<br />
Drox (get it at <a href="http://www.vginterface.com" target="_blank">www.vginterface.com</a>) has a few re-sizable button bars, and a boat load of extra ones. It also has a very nice info panel. No custom icons though. I'm not exactly sure what you are asking for there, but the reaction bar is hard-coded in the UI, and custom can only change the appearance, not the behavior. Drox does have the option of a horizontal or a vertical one. I use the vertical, and keep it on the right side of the screen; for characters that have stances, I put the stance bar right above. I'm using a re-sizable bar right below and also vertically oriented for my secondary finishers (since they don't show in the reaction bar). I've expanded it enough to also put clickies like bandages and the like, but you could just as easily put your barriers there. Another really nice Drox window is a toggled buff window that shows all your group members - you can drag all your targeted buffs to that, and don't have to target anyone, just click the buff next to their name.<br />
<br />
CoreUI is also a good one, but the current version is outdated, and the new one not released yet.
                  
