		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1229270">
                  
                  It matters little to me if these go live or not.<br />
<br />
I merely proposed a change, and EASY to implement change if these developers had any ounce of skill, to benefit the sorcerer class.<br />
<br />
I dont play a sorcerer as my &quot;main&quot; so I have no personal, direct investment in it, i merely wish to share my views.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
I really dont understand Daenor's anti-stance aurgument?<br />
<br />
The purpose of a stance is to adapt in-combat as you see fit, while not constantly changing. Battle conditions change, a offensive warrior may need to switch to defensive if an add happens, same for a bloodmage possibly switching to healing stance if an add happens and they need faster, stronger healing.<br />
<br />
I think this should apply to the sorcerer class as well. This gives them a easy-to-use method of adapting their playing style to meet the demands and challenges of the encounter.<br />
<br />
If nothing else, think of it as having &quot;options.&quot;<br />
<br />
More often or not, you will just, as you put it &quot;blow stuff up,&quot; but there should and hopefully will be cases where &quot;blow stuff up&quot; is not the best method.<br />
<br />
<br />
Considering the sorcerer's method of delivering damage is so one demensional as it is, atleast having some tactical decision in choosing your stance would be a step in the right direction.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
I honestly dont see how making a few simple changes would take all that much effort:<br />
<br />
Make flame barrier a static 20%+ to all damage, +30% to all energy costs.<br />
<br />
Make Force barrier a static % based mitigation buff, a scaling energy regeneration or better yet, an energy cost reduction on all nukes, and an AoE damage immunity. Eq2's devs are right down the hall... this was VERY easy for them to implement...<br />
<br />
Make Chromatic barrier increase spell identification and spell countering, and if our wards get changed, let it boost them.<br />
<br />
Create a Frost barrier with 20% reduce hate gain, a 15 second recharge rune with a 2 second root and 5 second 50% snare.<br />
<br />
<br />
If our developers lack the skill to create these in less than 5 hours time, i have simply lost all remaining faith in them and their game.<br />
<br />
They should use their resources and see if they can get some cooperation from the eq2 team.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
