		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1231096">
                  
                  <div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Drkpl2</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">
No need for a Sorc to change a stance, they have one, and only one really.  Kill anything they desire to kill.  The two barriers we do have play enough of a role for us if we get into a situation that we need to change them.<br />
<br />
With a few exceptions, I have never seen a Sorc try to tank, they kick back and fire spells from afar, why add something to a system when it would be much better for us to have things like Spell ID or Countering system worked on and all the bugs worked out on.  ( not trying to start a new subject with that one, or get us off track )</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
Barriers <u>are </u>stances.<br />
<br />
You must choose one or the other, you cannot have them active at the same time, and the offer different things that make them better for specific situations.<br />
<br />
All i am proposing is that we have them moved to a &quot;real&quot; stance format, and add in a new barrier, and make the current barriers more distinct.<br />
<br />
<br />
Im fully aware that other aspects of the game also need attention, but simply abandoning somthing on the long term so that they can work on something else for the short term is not good.<br />
<br />
Thats like suggesting the devs toss out any idea of improving crafting ever, because they are focused on raiding currently. Should raiding take prescedence? Sure, at this point it is needed. But does that mean they wont be able to improve crafting at a later time? I certainly hope not.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Spell ID and Countering, our Wards in regards to raiding, our way of dealing damage, and other such concerns definatly would be more important than looking into our Barriers, but the barriers could still be streamlined at a later date.<br />
<br />
<br />
Daeanor and Drkpl2, your personal conception and playstyle of the sorcerer is why you feel they should not have &quot;stances,&quot; despite the fact that they already do, rather than any concrete lore basis.<br />
<br />
I could rationalize how a sorcerer uses stances, just as you could rationalize a warrior, bloodmage, or psionicist using a stance, so neither of our aurguments can really hold merit on such conjectures.<br />
<br />
<br />
Instead, lets look at the facts:<br />
<br />
Flame Barrier, Force Barrier, and Chromatic Barrier.<br />
<br />
What do these do? They improve certain aspects of our class, but only one can be active at a time.<br />
<br />
Compare this to a stance.<br />
<br />
They improve certain aspects of a class, but only one can be active at a time. Some have trade offs, but sometimes it is not a direct + and - situation.<br />
<br />
An example would be the psionicist's Astral Form. It offers a 20% damage rune, with almost no &quot;limitations&quot; other than taking 20% more spiritual damage. So, really the &quot;draw back&quot; us using Astral Form is you are not getting the benefits that you would have gotten had you chosen another of your stances.<br />
<br />
This is how i think the sorcerer's barriers function.<br />
<br />
What is the draw back currently of using Flame Barrier? You're missing the added defense of Force Barrier or the added resistance and spell shielding of Chromatic.<br />
<br />
This is how my proposed stances work, exactly the same mechanic.<br />
<br />
You only have one active at a time, and the only &quot;draw back&quot; to using a particular barrier is that you are not recieving the other barrier's effects. So, you dont have to for instance have a &quot;lowers damage&quot; effect in my Force Barrier stance, because by choosing that stance instead of my version of the Flamre Barrier, you have already taken a potiential damage reduction.<br />
<br />
There ARE going to be situations where you will want to switch gear, and if there are not situations, then these developers have failed.<br />
<br />
In eq and eq2, a wizard cannot be going full &quot;burn&quot; on every single fight in existance.<br />
<br />
There are times you want to simply survive and deal damage, and you will deal more damage if you live through the encounter rather than trying to blow up the foe before it kills you.<br />
<br />
There are times you want to be as efficient as possible so you can deal more total damage rather than blow your load up front and have nothing left for the remainder of the fight.<br />
<br />
Then there are going to be times when you simply need to kill something as fast as possible.<br />
<br />
And, unique to the vanguard sorcerer, they devs have the potiential for situations where our anti-spell abilities will be highly valued.<br />
<br />
<br />
Despite how you play the sorcerer, that does not debunk the fact that there can certainly be situations where the basic &quot;kill it fast&quot; is not the best options, and i for one would hate to become a useless addition to the raid on those potientially rare, but possible, situations.<br />
<br />
That is why i propse they enhance and modify our Barriers so that we can raise up to meet these changing situations in a battle.<br />
<br />
<br />
Changing these barriers would be easier than introducing whole new spell lines that they would have to try to scale with contient, as we all have seen how poor the &quot;rank 1-5&quot; ect spell system can screw up.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
		<!-- edit note -->
			<div class="smallfont">			<hr size="1" style="color:#330066" />
				<em>
				Last edited by jhorry : October 9th, 2007 at <span class="time">10:13 AM</span>.
				
				</em>
			</div>
		<!-- / edit note -->
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt2">
		<img class="inlineimg" src="images/legacy_images/statusicon/user_offline.gif" alt="jhorry is offline" border="0" />


		
		
		
		&nbsp;
	</td>
	
